{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"d7b9d7ce3dd5cac5","type":"group","x":-2480,"y":-400,"width":1700,"height":760,"label":"replay phase"},
		{"id":"57cec0e8a798e047","type":"group","x":-2480,"y":-1200,"width":1260,"height":700,"label":"capture phase"},
		{
			"id":"aea435eed0b1e611",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Revise logic flow",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":-500,
			"y":-40,
			"width":460,
			"height":60
		},
		{
			"id":"01485a63b49a8e25",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Motivating example\n\n- client-side flaws may lead to business losses\n- E2E test may fail to detect these flaws\n- information in the GUI can lead to authorization bypass, complementing network tampering",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":-500,
			"y":120,
			"width":380,
			"height":440
		},
		{
			"id":"bd5e7fb304ca35cd",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Result modeled on a front-end centered BAC framework\n- OI/OP/OT are derived from the results of the study\n- and then mapped to existing CWEs",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":1000,
			"y":120,
			"width":400,
			"height":440
		},
		{
			"id":"1d9c0739d3c7f8fa",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## E2E AuthZ testing approach\n- Augmented Testing approach\n- based on HTTP proxy server and capture-replay mechanisms",
			"styleAttributes":{
				"border":"invisible",
				"textAlign":null
			},
			"x":0,
			"y":120,
			"width":480,
			"height":440
		},
		{
			"id":"25c11423136b3e28",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Applicability on Empirical study\n- 44 applications\n- 1 user workflow per application",
			"styleAttributes":{
				"border":"invisible",
				"textAlign":null
			},
			"x":560,
			"y":120,
			"width":340,
			"height":440
		},
		{
			"id":"f5a5db7bfc190a01",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Authorization Flaws in Commercial SPA-Based Web Applications: An Empirical Study through Front-End Analysis",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","border":"invisible"},
			"x":2680,
			"y":-580,
			"width":776,
			"height":160
		},
		{
			"id":"4ee8f2e29d2003d4",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"Problems:\n- \"web front-ends\" is too general, we focus on SPA\n- if we study the \"role\", why didn't we focus on apps that are known to be vulnerable (from CVEs)?\n- The title must refer to features in commercial apps\n- We should highlight the novel approach",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":1880,
			"y":-300,
			"width":715,
			"height":300
		},
		{
			"id":"164b3b00d1bc62a8",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Authorization-Centered End-to-End Testing for Detecting Authorization Flaws in Web Applications",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","border":"invisible"},
			"x":2720,
			"y":-340,
			"width":676,
			"height":160
		},
		{
			"id":"0147c7d8dcc8b485",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# On the Role of Web Front-Ends in Broken Access Control. Vulnerabilities: An Empirical Study",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","border":"invisible"},
			"x":1880,
			"y":-580,
			"width":715,
			"height":200
		},
		{
			"id":"97bb4c8791c62880",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Augmented Authorization Testing: Generating End-to-End Security Tests from User Workflows",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","border":"invisible"},
			"x":2720,
			"y":-140,
			"width":676,
			"height":150
		},
		{
			"id":"3b56c8eea3967d6d",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Current logic flow",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":-500,
			"y":-580,
			"width":460,
			"height":60
		},
		{
			"id":"19f4f7261c8cd564",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Motivating example\n\n- client-side flaws may lead to business losses",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":-500,
			"y":-440,
			"width":380,
			"height":300
		},
		{
			"id":"6b7513eb2143ee26",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Front-end centered BAC framework\n- from authorization-related CWE to OI/OP/OT",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":0,
			"y":-440,
			"width":400,
			"height":300
		},
		{
			"id":"eb37d52777f39b75",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Tampering techniques\n- JavaScript Component Hijacking\n- HTTP response tampering",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":520,
			"y":-440,
			"width":420,
			"height":300
		},
		{
			"id":"64a3d0c663095fb8",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Empirical study\n- methodology\n- testing protocol\n- results",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":1020,
			"y":-440,
			"width":420,
			"height":300
		},
