			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","shape":"pill"},
			"x":-1100,
			"y":-200,
			"width":300,
			"height":160
		},
		{
			"id":"388f78ebb3d00df9",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# 🤖",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible","textAlign":"center"},
			"x":-2460,
			"y":-160,
			"width":80,
			"height":80
		},
		{
			"id":"7814a86d03561607",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# 3. Test generation phase",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","border":"invisible"},
			"x":-2900,
			"y":480,
			"width":420,
			"height":120
		},
		{
			"id":"c5866dbc28629440",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"- image regression testing-based oracle\n- we compare screenshots and highlight differences in user workflows that may violate the user privileges\n- test are generated considering altered HTTP responses",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","border":"invisible"},
			"x":-2480,
			"y":440,
			"width":1200,
			"height":200
		},
		{
			"id":"8f200e522722a525",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# from \"we tamper with 44 apps using known techniques and we find xxx BAC\"",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","shape":"pill"},
			"x":-270,
			"y":-1140,
			"width":540,
			"height":300
		},
		{
			"id":"9ced7a6b602fb4f6",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# to \"we propose a semi-automatic approach to generate authorization-centered E2E tests. It is validated in 44 apps and found xxx BAC\"",
			"styleAttributes":{"textAlign":"center","shape":"pill"},
			"x":390,
			"y":-1140,
			"width":820,
			"height":300
		},
		{
			"id":"440cd800308d93d4",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"- register worflow \n(eg. home > button 1 > page 2 > ...)\n- produce screenshots after each action",
			"styleAttributes":{
				"textAlign":"center",
				"shape":null,
				"border":"invisible"
			},
			"x":-2340,
			"y":-780,
			"width":460,
			"height":200,
			"color":"2"
		},
		{
			"id":"5a97235530738cc9",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Advantages:\n\n## - we test samples of user workflows, not the all app\n## - it can work regardless of the back-end AND the front-end technologies being used (!)\n## - the approach can be used during development to properly test workflows of new feature",
			"styleAttributes":{"border":"invisible"},
			"x":-2440,
			"y":800,
			"width":1020,
			"height":480
		},
		{
			"id":"2dc8ee1a27fe9c34",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Is automatic click blocked ??",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-3160,
			"y":-200,
			"width":360,
			"height":160,
			"color":"1"
		}
